Description: Model Context Protocol server for Nextcloud integration
 Nextcloud MCP Server implements the Model Context Protocol (MCP) so that
 AI assistants and LLM-based agents can interact with a Nextcloud instance:
 Notes, Calendar (CalDAV + VTODO tasks), Contacts (CardDAV), Tables, WebDAV,
 Deck, Cookbook, Mail, News, Talk and Collectives.
 .
 This package provides both the importable nextcloud_mcp_server Python
 module and the nextcloud-mcp-server console script entry point.
 .
 NOTE: this package's declared dependencies do not yet cover 6 hard
 runtime requirements that have no Debian package available in the apt
 repo yet (fastembed, anthropic, langchain-text-splitters, pymupdf4llm,
 pypdfium2, qdrant-client).
 See /usr/share/doc/nextcloud-mcp-server/README.Debian for details.
